  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "The Cpx (conjugative pilus expression) two-component system responds to protein misfolding stress in the periplasm and inner membrane. The sensor kinase CpxA detects envelope stress signals including misfolded pili, alkaline pH, changes in membrane composition, and accumulation of misfolded periplasmic proteins. Upon activation, CpxA autophosphorylates and transfers phosphate to the response regulator CpxR, which activates transcription of >100 genes involved in protein folding, degradation, and envelope homeostasis. The Cpx response overlaps with but is distinct from the \u03c3E envelope stress response, with CpxAR primarily sensing inner membrane and periplasmic stress while \u03c3E responds to outer membrane stress. Key Cpx target genes include periplasmic proteases (DegP), protein folding factors (DsbA), and pilus assembly inhibitors. This flowchart illustrates stress detection, signal transduction through the two-component system, and the protective responses that restore envelope integrity.",
  "id": "ecoli_periplasmic_stress",
